702
00:37:07,258 --> 00:37:11,539
Back on land in Saint Augustine,
Dr. Kathleen Deagan

703
00:37:11,563 --> 00:37:14,675
and a team of archaeologists
from the University of Florida

704
00:37:14,699 --> 00:37:17,344
have unearthed a major new find

705
00:37:17,368 --> 00:37:19,880
about what happened
to those first settlers

706
00:37:19,904 --> 00:37:23,751
who came over
with Pedro Menéndez.

707
00:37:23,775 --> 00:37:24,819
- I've always thought
it was like

708
00:37:24,843 --> 00:37:28,756
having a 2,000-piece
jigsaw puzzle,

709
00:37:28,780 --> 00:37:30,424
but you don't know
that the picture

710
00:37:30,448 --> 00:37:32,359
is supposed to look like.

711
00:37:32,383 --> 00:37:33,894
- Deagan has already uncovered

712
00:37:33,918 --> 00:37:36,497
some of the most pivotal
archaeological sites

713
00:37:36,521 --> 00:37:39,366
in this country's early history.

714
00:37:39,390 --> 00:37:40,801
- It's really only
through archeology

715
00:37:40,825 --> 00:37:44,772
that we know
what regular people did.

